The '''2012 Tour de Pologne''' was the 69th running of the [[Tour de Pologne]] cycling stage race. It started on 10 July in [[Karpacz]] and ended on 16 July in [[Krak<U+00F3>w]], after seven stages.<ref name="Preview">{{cite news|url=http://tourdepologne.pl/en/?showNewsLite=117|title="Preview" to the 2012 Route|work=[[Tour de Pologne]]|publisher=Lang Team Sp. z o.o.|date=8 March 2012|accessdate=10 July 2012}}</ref> It was the 19th race of the [[2012 UCI World Tour]] season.

The race was won by {{ct|LIQ|2012}} rider [[Moreno Moser]],<ref name="End">{{cite news|url=http://tourdepologne.pl/?showNewsLite=171|title=Moser zwyci<U+0119>zc<U+0105> 69. Tour de Pologne!|language=Polish|trans_title=Moser winner of the 69th Tour de Pologne!|work=[[Tour de Pologne]]|publisher=Lang Team Sp. z o.o.|date=16 July 2012|accessdate=17 July 2012}}</ref> who claimed the leader's yellow jersey after winning the penultimate stage, and maintained the lead of the race until its conclusion; he also won the race's opening stage, his first wins at World Tour level. Moser's winning margin over runner-up [[Micha<U+0142> Kwiatkowski (cyclist)|Micha<U+0142> Kwiatkowski]] of {{ct|OPQ|2012}} <U+2013> the highest-placed Polish rider <U+2013> was five seconds,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.omegapharma-quickstep.com/en/news/show/tour-de-pologne-stage-7-stybar-makes-the-break-kwiatkowski-finishes-2nd-in-gc/752|title=Stybar Makes the Break, Kwiatkowski Finishes 2nd in GC|work={{ct|OPQ|2012}}|publisher=Decolef|date=16 July 2012|accessdate=17 July 2012}}</ref> and {{ct|SKY|2012}}'s [[Sergio Henao]] completed the podium,<ref name="Sky end">{{cite news|url=http://www.teamsky.com/article/0,27290,26118_7904893,00.html|title=Strong finish in Poland|work={{ct|SKY|2012}}|publisher=[[BSkyB]]|date=16 July 2012|accessdate=17 July 2012}}</ref> eleven seconds down on Kwiatkowski and sixteen behind Moser.

In the race's other classifications, {{ct|VCD|2012}} rider [[Tomasz Marczy<U+0144>ski]] won the King of the Mountains classification,<ref name="End"/> {{ct|SKY|2012|nolink=yes}}'s [[Ben Swift]] won the white jersey for the points classification after winning two stages during the event,<ref name="Sky end"/> and [[Adrian Kurek]] of {{ct|UNA|2012}} won the intermediate sprints classification,<ref name="End"/> for the second year in succession. As well as their two stage victories, {{ct|SKY|2012|nolink=yes}} finished at the head of the teams classification.<ref name="Sky end"/>

==Schedule==
Aside from entering the Czech Republic during the third stage, the race stages started and ended in Polish locations.<ref name="Preview"/>
