==Participating teams==
As the Tour de Pologne was a UCI World Tour event, all eighteen [[UCI ProTour#List of current UCI ProTeams|UCI ProTeam]]s were invited automatically and obligated to send a squad. Along with [[Polish Cycling Federation|Team Poland BG<U+017B>]] <U+2013> the Polish national team <U+2013> six other squads were given wildcard places into the race, and as such, formed the event's 25-team peloton.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tourdepologne.pl/en/?showNewsLite=126|title=25 teams to start|work=[[Tour de Pologne]]|publisher=Lang Team Sp. z o.o.|date=23 April 2012|accessdate=10 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.velonation.com/News/ID/11710/Tour-of-Poland-presents-tough-mountainous-course-for-2012-edition.aspx|title=Tour of Poland presents tough, mountainous course for 2012 edition|work=VeloNation|publisher=VeloNation LLC|first=Ben|last=Atkins|date=25 April 2012|accessdate=10 July 2012}}</ref>

The twenty-five teams that competed in the race were:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/tour-de-pologne-2012/start-list|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|accessdate=10 July 2012|title=Tour de Pologne 2012 start list}}</ref>

